    {
      "id": "section-2",
      "type": "split",
      "layout": "text-left",
      "title": "Health Fact #1",
      "content": {
        "text": "92% of the world’s population lives in places where air pollution exceeds safe limits.",
        "media": {
          "type": "image",
          "url": "/images/training/module-1/lecture-4/26.jpg",
          "alt": "Example Image",
          "isClickable": true,
          "caption": "Areas in yellow, red, orange and purple exceed the WHO’s safety limits for air pollution."
        }
      },
      "divider": true
    },
    {
      "id": "section-3",
      "type": "split",
      "layout": "text-right",
      "title": "Health Fact #2",
      "content": {
        "text": "Air pollution is the fourth-largest threat to human health after high blood pressure, dietary risks and smoking.",
        "media": {
          "type": "image",
          "url": "/images/training/module-1/lecture-4/27.jpg",
          "alt": "Example Image",
          "isClickable": true,
          "caption": ""
        }
      },
      "divider": true
    },
    {
      "id": "section-4",
      "type": "split",
      "layout": "text-left",
      "title": "Health Fact #3",
      "content": {
        "text": "In 2017, approximately 10% of all deaths worldwide were from air pollution related diseases.",
        "media": {
          "type": "image",
          "url": "/images/training/module-1/lecture-4/28.jpg",
          "alt": "Example Image",
          "isClickable": true,
          "caption": ""
        }
      },
      "divider": true
    },
    {
      "id": "section-5",
      "type": "split",
      "layout": "text-right",
      "title": "Health Fact #4",
      "content": {
        "text": "In 2017, it is estimated that air pollution reduced worldwide life expectancy by an average of 20 months.",
        "media": {
          "type": "image",
          "url": "/images/training/module-1/lecture-4/29.jpg",
